Class MoonEphemElement

    public class MoonEphemElement

      • mutualPhenomena

        public java.lang.String mutualPhenomena
        Holds a description of the mutual phenomena in a given instant. Format is ECLIPSED/OCCULTED BY and the name of the object producing the event. The object can be another satellite or the mother planet, the last case only when the eclipse/occultation is currently partial.

        public double longitudeOfCentralMeridian
        Longitude of central meridian in radians. For giant planets (Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune) the value will be refered to system III of coordinates.

      • brightLimbAngle

        public float brightLimbAngle
        Bright limb angle in radians.

      • subsolarLatitude

        public double subsolarLatitude
        Subsolar latitude. In case of Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune, can be considered the ring plane ilumination angle. It depends on the relative position of the Sun.

      • subsolarLongitude

        public double subsolarLongitude
        Subsolar longitude. It depends on the relative position of the Sun. In giant planets the value is refered to System III of coordinates.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MoonEphemElement

        public MoonEphemElement(java.lang.String nom,
                double ra,
                double dec,
                double dist,
                double dist_sun,
                double azi,
                double ele,
                float ill,
                float elo,
                boolean ecl,
                boolean ocl,
                boolean tran,
                boolean shadow_transiting,
                boolean inf,
                double x,
                double y,
                double z,
                double x_sun,
                double y_sun,
                double z_sun)
        Constructs a MoonEphem object giving all the data except angular radius, magnitude, ecliptic position, phase angle, and axis orientation.
        Parameters:
        nom - Name of the satellite.
        ra - Right ascension.
        dec - Declination.
        dist - Distance.
        dist_sun - Distance from the Sun.
        azi - Azimuth.
        ele - Elevation.
        ill - Illumination fraction.
        elo - Elongation in radians.
        ecl - True if the satellite is not illuminated.
        ocl - True if the satellite is oculted.
        tran - True is the satellite is transiting as seen by the observer.
        shadow_transiting - True if the shadow is transiting.
        inf - True if z is lower than 0.0.
        x - X position in units of equatorial radii respect to planet and the sky plane.
        y - Y position in units of equatorial radii respect to planet and the sky plane.
        z - Z position in units of equatorial radii respect to planet and the sky plane.
        x_sun - X position in units of equatorial radii respect to Sun and the sky plane.
        y_sun - Y position in units of equatorial radii respect to Sun and the sky plane.
        z_sun - Z position in units of equatorial radii respect to Sun and the sky plane.
